The paper proposes a deep learning approach for multi-object tracking, which involves learning a deep conditional random field (CRF) network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves modeling long-term dependencies among detection results, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves optimizing the CRF inference using the gradient descent algorithm, which suggests that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on challenging MOT datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
